==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Acquittal
<hw>Ac*quit"tal</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
act of acquitting; discharge from debt or obligation;
acquittance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>A setting free, or deliverance from
the charge of an offense, by verdict of a jury or sentence of a
court.</def> <rj><au>Bouvier.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Acquittance</ent>⟦br⟧
